{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_1676f89cd7de4e5384136251","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Task: Port User Summary Aggregation\n2\t\n3\t## Goal\n4\tPort the user summary cron job from Python to TypeScript — the most complex module in the system. Reads all user data from GCS, matches evaluations to applicants using Levenshtein + name decomposition, computes reporting status, and writes aggregated summary files.\n5\t\n6\t## Read These Files First\n7\t1. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/reporting/user_summary.py` (full file, ~750 lines) — the source to port\n8\t2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/reporting/reporting-utils.ts` — `getReportingStatus()`, `getTtcList()` (created in Task 4.1)\n9\t3. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/reporting/matching.ts` — `levenshteinB()` (created in Task 4.2)\n10\t4. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/ttc-portal-user.ts` — user data model\n11\t5. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/gcs.ts` — `readJson()`, `writeJson()`, `listFiles()`, `GCS_PATHS`\n12\t6. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/mock-data.ts` — `MOCK_SUMMARY_DATA` and `MOCK_REPORTS_DATA` shapes (these are the output format to match)\n13\t\n14\t## Changes Required\n15\t\n16\t**Create `app/utils/reporting/user-summary.ts`:**\n17\t\n18\tPort `Reporting.load_user_summary()` as `async function loadUserSummary()`.\n19\t\n20\t**High-level steps (matching Python structure):**\n21\t\n22\t1. Read TTC list from GCS\n23\t2. Load existing summary from GCS (or empty dict if not found)\n24\t3. List all user JSON files in `user_data/` prefix\n25\t4. For each user file:\n26\t   - Parse JSON, iterate form_data by form_type and form_instance\n27\t   - Skip `default` instances\n28\t   - Apply `reporting_fields` whitelist (Python lines 76-116)\n29\t   - Calculate initial reporting_status via `getReportingStatus()`\n30\t   - Count prereq_no answers, list lengths\n31\t   - Attach TTC metadata\n32\t   - Parse form_instance key for email extraction (Python lines 223-235)\n33\t   - Build nested structure: `_user_data_by_email[email][form_type][instance]`\n34\t5. KEYRESET: Clear past evaluation assignments (Python lines 252-293)\n35\t6. Evaluation matching — O(n²) loop (Python lines 298-525):\n36\t   - For each `ttc_evaluation`, try to match to a `ttc_application` user\n37\t   - Match criteria: email exact match OR name Levenshtein ≤ 1 with multi-word decomposition\n38\t   - On match: add to `evaluations` dict, update counts, check teaching_readiness, ratings_below_3\n39\t   - Track both current-TTC and lifetime evaluations separately\n40\t7. Post-TTC feedback matching (Python lines 528-650):\n41\t   - Similar to #6 but matches `post_ttc_feedback_form` to `post_ttc_self_evaluation_form`\n42\t   - Levenshtein threshold = 2 (more lenient)\n43\t   - Also matches by `i_course_start` date\n44\t8. Post-Sahaj feedback matching (Python lines 650+):\n45\t   - Same pattern as #7 for Sahaj forms\n46\t9. Write output files:\n47\t   - `user_summary_by_user.json` — the full aggregated data\n48\t   - `user_summary_by_form_type.json` — **intentional divergence**: legacy only writes `_by_user`, but TS also writes `_by_form_type` because the summary page JS needs it\n49\t\n50\t**Also create route handlers:**\n51\t- `app/reporting/user-summary/load/route.ts` — GET: `requireAdminOrCron()`, POST: `requireAdmin()`\n52\t- `app/jobs/reporting/user-summary/load/route.ts` — same auth, alias\n53\t- `app/reporting/user-summary/get-by-user/route.ts` — GET: `requireAdminOrCron()`, reads `USER_SUMMARY_BY_USER`\n54\t\n55\t## Constraints\n56\t- Port logic EXACTLY — do not optimize the O(n²) matching loop\n57\t- Do NOT add `_by_form_type` generation logic that wasn't in the original — instead, transform `_by_user` into `_by_form_type` by restructuring the same data (invert the key hierarchy)\n58\t- Keep `text/plain` content-type on get-by-user response\n59\t- `DATA_RETENTION_DAYS = 730` (from constants.py line 66) — skip records older than this\n60\t\n61\t## Verification\n62\t- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n63\t\n64\t## Completion\n65\t- Commit with message: `feat: port user summary aggregation with evaluation matching`\n66\t- Report: files changed, verification result\n67\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3af0d9ba-b901-4246-aa27-51959c42c364","uuid":"30b0d897-7ec8-43e7-aa52-da925167b9c8","timestamp":"2026-04-06T11:32:20.698Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/.agent/tasks/task-4.3-user-summary.md","content":"# Task: Port User Summary Aggregation\n\n## Goal\nPort the user summary cron job from Python to TypeScript — the most complex module in the system. Reads all user data from GCS, matches evaluations to applicants using Levenshtein + name decomposition, computes reporting status, and writes aggregated summary files.\n\n## Read These Files First\n1. `/Users/m/Downloads/europe-ttp-master@44c225683f8/reporting/user_summary.py` (full file, ~750 lines) — the source to port\n2. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/reporting/reporting-utils.ts` — `getReportingStatus()`, `getTtcList()` (created in Task 4.1)\n3. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/reporting/matching.ts` — `levenshteinB()` (created in Task 4.2)\n4. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/ttc-portal-user.ts` — user data model\n5. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/utils/gcs.ts` — `readJson()`, `writeJson()`, `listFiles()`, `GCS_PATHS`\n6. `/Users/m/ttp-split-experiment/app/api/admin/mock-data.ts` — `MOCK_SUMMARY_DATA` and `MOCK_REPORTS_DATA` shapes (these are the output format to match)\n\n## Changes Required\n\n**Create `app/utils/reporting/user-summary.ts`:**\n\nPort `Reporting.load_user_summary()` as `async function loadUserSummary()`.\n\n**High-level steps (matching Python structure):**\n\n1. Read TTC list from GCS\n2. Load existing summary from GCS (or empty dict if not found)\n3. List all user JSON files in `user_data/` prefix\n4. For each user file:\n   - Parse JSON, iterate form_data by form_type and form_instance\n   - Skip `default` instances\n   - Apply `reporting_fields` whitelist (Python lines 76-116)\n   - Calculate initial reporting_status via `getReportingStatus()`\n   - Count prereq_no answers, list lengths\n   - Attach TTC metadata\n   - Parse form_instance key for email extraction (Python lines 223-235)\n   - Build nested structure: `_user_data_by_email[email][form_type][instance]`\n5. KEYRESET: Clear past evaluation assignments (Python lines 252-293)\n6. Evaluation matching — O(n²) loop (Python lines 298-525):\n   - For each `ttc_evaluation`, try to match to a `ttc_application` user\n   - Match criteria: email exact match OR name Levenshtein ≤ 1 with multi-word decomposition\n   - On match: add to `evaluations` dict, update counts, check teaching_readiness, ratings_below_3\n   - Track both current-TTC and lifetime evaluations separately\n7. Post-TTC feedback matching (Python lines 528-650):\n   - Similar to #6 but matches `post_ttc_feedback_form` to `post_ttc_self_evaluation_form`\n   - Levenshtein threshold = 2 (more lenient)\n   - Also matches by `i_course_start` date\n8. Post-Sahaj feedback matching (Python lines 650+):\n   - Same pattern as #7 for Sahaj forms\n9. Write output files:\n   - `user_summary_by_user.json` — the full aggregated data\n   - `user_summary_by_form_type.json` — **intentional divergence**: legacy only writes `_by_user`, but TS also writes `_by_form_type` because the summary page JS needs it\n\n**Also create route handlers:**\n- `app/reporting/user-summary/load/route.ts` — GET: `requireAdminOrCron()`, POST: `requireAdmin()`\n- `app/jobs/reporting/user-summary/load/route.ts` — same auth, alias\n- `app/reporting/user-summary/get-by-user/route.ts` — GET: `requireAdminOrCron()`, reads `USER_SUMMARY_BY_USER`\n\n## Constraints\n- Port logic EXACTLY — do not optimize the O(n²) matching loop\n- Do NOT add `_by_form_type` generation logic that wasn't in the original — instead, transform `_by_user` into `_by_form_type` by restructuring the same data (invert the key hierarchy)\n- Keep `text/plain` content-type on get-by-user response\n- `DATA_RETENTION_DAYS = 730` (from constants.py line 66) — skip records older than this\n\n## Verification\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` must pass\n\n## Completion\n- Commit with message: `feat: port user summary aggregation with evaluation matching`\n- Report: files changed, verification result\n","numLines":67,"startLine":1,"totalLines":67}}}
