y exists.\n\nHowever, in the TS port, `processCurrent` is explicitly initialized to `false` at the start of each ve iteration (line 377). This is actually BETTER than the Python behavior. The task says \"Port logic EXACTLY — do not optimize the O(n²) matching loop\" but initializing to false is actually more correct.\n\nHmm wait, I'm being too pedantic here. Let me focus on actual bugs.\n\n**Bug 4: Evaluation matching - reporting status update is OUTSIDE the `is_form_submitted` check in Python**\n\nLook at Python lines 464-517:\n```python\nif _e.get('is_form_submitted', False):\n    if _process_current:\n        ...evaluations_submitted_count += 1\n    if _process_lifetime:\n        ...lifetime_evaluations_submitted_count += 1\n        # teaching readiness processing\n        ...\n        # ratings processing\n        ...\n\n# [START] [reporting_fields] Processing application status\n# If no of submitted evaluations touches 3, then set status to complete\napp_status, eval_status = reporting_utils.get_reporting_status(\n    'ttc_application', ...)\n```\n\nNote that the reporting status update (lines 506-517) is OUTSIDE the `if _e.get('is_form_submitted', False)` block. It's at the same indentation level as the `if _e.get('is_form_submitted', False)` block, meaning it runs on EVERY match, not just submitted ones.\n\nIn the TS port (lines 422-498):\n```typescript\nif (e['is_form_submitted']) {\n    if (processCurrent) {\n        ...evaluations_submitted_count += 1\n        // teaching readiness\n        ...\n        // ratings\n        ...\n        if (processLifetime) {\n            ...\n        } else if (processLifetime) {\n            ...\n        }\n    }\n    // Update reporting status\n    const [appStatus2, evalStatus2] = getReportingStatus(...)\n    ...\n}\n```\n\n**BUG FOUND!** In the TS port, the reporting status update (`getReportingStatus` call at lines 488-497) is INSIDE the `if (e['is_form_submitted'])` block. In the Python source, this is OUTSIDE the `is_form_submitted` check. The reporting status should be updated on every match, not just when the evaluation is submitted.\n\nLet me verify this by re-reading the indentation carefully.\n\nPython lines 463-517:\n```python\n                                # If evaluation is submitted increment the count.\n                                if _e.get('is_form_submitted', False):\n                                    if _process_current:\n                                        ...count += 1\n                                    if _process_lifetime:\n                                        ...lifetime_count += 1\n                                        # teaching readiness processing\n                                        ...\n                                    # ratings processing\n                                    for _q in _ed:\n                                        ...\n                                # [START] [reporting_fields] Processing application status\n                                # If no of submitted evaluations touches 3, then set status to complete\n                                app_status, eval_status = reporting_utils.get_reporting_status(\n```\n\nThe `app_status, eval_status` line is at 32-space indentation, while `if _e.get('is_form_submitted', False):` is at 32-space indentation too. So the status update IS inside the `if _e.get('is_form_submitted')` block because lines 493-517 are at 36+ space indentation (inside the if block).\n\nWait let me recount...\n\nLine 464: `                                if _e.get('is_form_submitted', False):` — this is at 32 spaces\n\nLine 466: `                                    _user_data_by_email... += 1` — this is at 36 spaces (inside the if)\n\nLine 506-508:\n```python\n                                # [START] [reporting_fields] Processing application status\n                                app_status, eval_status = reporting_utils.get_reporting_status(\n```\n\nThis is at 32 spaces, which is the SAME level as the `if _e.get('is_form_submitted', False):` line. This means the reporting status update is OUTSIDE the `is_form_submitted` check.\n\nActually wait, I need to look more carefully at the raw indentation. Let me look at the actual file content.\n\nLines 463-517:\n```\n                                if _e.get('is_form_submitted', False):\n                                    if _process_current:\n                                        ...\n                                    if _process_lifetime:\n                                        ...\n\n                                    # [START] [reporting_fields] Processing readiness by evaluators\n                                    ...\n                                    # [END] [reporting_fields] Processing readiness by evaluators\n                                    \n                                    # [START] [reporting_fields] Processing ratings by evaluator\n                                    for _q in _ed:\n                                        ...\n                                    # [END] [reporting_fields] Processing ratings by evaluator\n\n                                # [START] [reporting_fields] Processing application status\n                                app_status, eval_status = reporting_utils.get_reporting_status(\n```\n\nOK so lines 470-504 are at 36-space indentation (inside the `if _e.get('is_form_submitted')` block). Then the comment at line 506 drops back to 32-space indentation, which is OUTSIDE the `is_form_submitted` if block but still INSIDE the match condition block.\n\nSo in Python, the reporting status update runs for EVERY match (even non-submitted ones), while in the TS port, it only runs when `e['is_form_submitted']` is true.\n\nThis is a **bug** in the TS port. The reporting status should be updated outside the `is_form_submitted` check.\n\n**Bug 5: In the `is_form_submitted` block, the processCurrent/processLifetime nesting is wrong**\n\nLet me look at this more carefully. In Python (lines 463-504):\n\n```python\nif _e.get('is_form_submitted', False):\n    if _process_current:\n        evaluations_submitted_count += 1\n    if _process_lifetime:\n        lifetime_evaluations_submitted_count += 1\n\n    # teaching readiness (runs for BOTH processCurrent and processLifetime)\n    _teaching_readiness = _ed.get(...)\n    if _teaching_readiness != '':\n        if _process_current:\n            ...\n        if _process_lifetime:\n            ...\n        if _teaching_readiness != 'ready_now':\n            if _process_current:\n                ...\n            if _process_lifetime:\n                ...\n\n    # ratings (runs for BOTH processCurrent and processLifetime)\n    for _q in _ed:\n        if ...:\n            if _process_current:\n                ...\n            if _process_lifetime:\n                ...\n```\n\nIn the TS port (lines 422-485):\n\n```typescript\nif (e['is_form_submitted']) {\n    if (processCurrent) {\n        afiReporting['evaluations_submitted_count'] += 1;\n        \n        // Teaching readiness\n        const teachingReadiness = ...;\n        if (teachingReadiness) {\n            ... current teaching readiness\n            if (processLifetime) {\n                ... lifetime teaching readiness\n            }\n        }\n        \n        // Ratings\n        for (const q of Object.keys(ed)) {\n            if (...) {\n                if (processCurrent) {\n                    ... current ratings\n                }\n                if (processLifetime) {\n                    ... lifetime ratings\n                }\n            }\n        }\n    } else if (processLifetime) {\n        // lifetime only\n        ... lifetime evaluations_submitted_count\n        ... lifetime teaching readiness\n        ... lifetime ratings\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**BUG FOUND!** The nesting structure is wrong. In the Python code:\n1. `evaluations_submitted_count` increment for `processCurrent` and `processLifetime` are independent (two separate if blocks)\n2. Teaching readiness processing for `processCurrent` and `processLifetime` are independent (two separate if blocks)\n3. Ratings processing for `processCurrent` and `processLifetime` are independent (two separate if blocks)\n\nIn the TS port, the structure is:\n1. If `processCurrent`: do current count, teaching readiness (with processLifetime nested inside), and ratings\n2. Else if `processLifetime`: do lifetime count, teaching readiness, and ratings\n\nThis means:\n- In the TS port, when `processCurrent` is true and `processLifetime` is true, the `lifetime_evaluations_submitted_count` is NOT incremented (because it's inside the `processCurrent` block, nested under `if (processLifetime)` which is inside `if (teachingReadiness)`).\n- Actually wait, let me re-read the TS code more carefully...\n\nTS lines 422-485:\n```typescript\nif (e['is_form_submitted']) {\n    if (processCurrent) {\n        // line 425: current evaluations_submitted_count += 1\n\n        // Teaching readiness (current)\n        const teachingReadiness = String(ed['i_volunteer_teaching_readiness'] || '');\n        if (teachingReadiness) {\n            // current teaching readiness\n            if (processLifetime) {\n                // lifetime teaching readiness (inside processCurrent && teachingReadiness)\n            }\n        }\n\n        // Ratings\n        for (...) {\n            // current ratings\n            if (processLifetime) {\n                // lifetime ratings\n            }\n        }\n    } else if (processLifetime) {\n        // processCurrent is false but processLifetime is true\n        // lifetime evaluations_submitted_count\n        // lifetime teaching readiness\n        // lifetime ratings\n    }\n}\n```\n\nSo the issue is:\n1. When `processCurrent=true` AND `processLifetime=true`:\n   - `evaluations_submitted_count` (current) is incremented ✓\n   - `lifetime_evaluations_submitted_count` is NOT incremented ✗ (it's in the else if branch)\n   - Current teaching readiness is processed ✓\n   - Lifetime teaching readiness is processed ✓ (nested inside)\n   - Current ratings are processed ✓\n   - Lifetime ratings are processed ✓ (nested inside)\n\n2. When `processCurrent=false` AND `processLifetime=true`:\n   - `evaluations_submitted_count` (current) is NOT incremented ✓ (correct, since not current)\n   - `lifetime_evaluations_submitted_count` IS incremented ✓\n   - Lifetime teaching readiness is processed ✓\n   - Lifetime ratings are processed ✓\n\nSo the bug is: when both `processCurrent` and `processLifetime` are true, `lifetime_evaluations_submitted_count` is not incremented. In Python, it would be incremented because the two if blocks are independent.\n\nThis is a real bug!\n\nAlso, there's a subtler issue: when `processCurrent=true` and `processLifetime=true`, the lifetime teaching readiness is only processed if `teachingReadiness` is truthy (since it's inside `if (teachingReadiness)`). In Python, the lifetime teaching readiness is also only processed if `teachingReadiness` is truthy, but the count increment for `lifetime_evaluations_submitted_count` is outside the `teachingReadiness` check. So the counts and the teaching readiness processing have different conditions, which is correct in Python but buggy in TS.\n\n**Bug 6: Missing `i_course_start` date matching in post-TTC and post-Sahaj feedback matching**\n\nThe Python code for post-TTC feedback (lines 540, 543-549, 564-572) parses `i_course_start` dates for both the evaluator and the candidate:\n```python\n_cd = _ed.get('i_course_start', '').strip()\n...\ntry:\n    if len(_cd) == 10:\n        _t_cd = datetime.strptime(_cd, '%m/%d/%Y')\n    else:\n        _t_cd = datetime.strptime(_cd, '%m/%d/%y')\n    _cd = _t_cd\nexcept Exception as exception:\n    pass\n```\n\nAnd for the candidate:\n```python\n_acd = _ad.get('i_course_start', '').strip()\ntry:\n    ...\nexcept:\n    pass\n```\n\nHowever, looking at the match conditions in Python (lines 589-609), the `_cd` and